What is Docker?

Docker is platform for packaging, distribution and the running application.

Three main concepts in a Docker Scenario:

1. Images:- Something we can packaging inside a image such as application.
2. Registry: It is an repository to store the images. It can be local and remote.
3. Containers: Run time entinty

# To pull images
$ sudo docker pull <image_name>

# List docker images
$ sudo docker images

# Run the container
<Format> sudo docker run --name <container_name> -p <ExposePort:InternalPort> -d <Image_name>
Example: $ sudo docker run --name MyNginxWebServerExposed -p 8080:80 -d nginx

